.SS "2.6. Where can I report bugs?"
.IX Subsection "2.6. Where can I report bugs?"
First collect the required information using the following command:
.PP
.Vb 1
\& :source $VIMRUNTIME/bugreport.vim
.Ve
.PP
Now send the resulting text from the above command to the bugs@vim.org
e\-mail address. There is also a public bug tracker available at
http://code.google.com/p/vim/issues/list. A copy of each message there
will be forwarded to the Vim Development list.
.PP
The Vim Development mailing list (see Question 2.2) is a good place to
discuss general bugs.  If the bug you find is with syntax highlighting,
a runtime file, or some other \*(L"added feature\*(R" (i.e. not directly
programmed into vim), attempt to inform the maintainer of that feature.
His e\-mail address will be mentioned at the top of the corresponding
runtime file.
.PP
For more information, read
.PP
\&\fB:help bug-reports\fR
.SS "2.7. Where can the \s-1FAQ\s0 be found?"
.IX Subsection "2.7. Where can the FAQ be found?"
The \s-1FAQ\s0 can be found at http://vimhelp.appspot.com/vim_faq.txt.html.
It will be auto-generated from the source that is managed in the github
repository http://www.github.com/chrisbra/vim_faq (Patches are welcome).
.PP
The repository also includes the faq in different formats, e.g. manpage,
pdf file, html file, plain text version and a version in vim help format.
.PP
A slightly older version (which doesn't seem to get updated anymore) can
still be found at VimOnline (vim.sf.net).
.SS "2.8. What if I don't find an answer in this \s-1FAQ\s0?"
.IX Subsection "2.8. What if I don't find an answer in this FAQ?"
This \s-1FAQ\s0 covers mainly Vim-specific questions. You may find more
information suitable for most Vi clones by reading the Vi \s-1FAQ.\s0 It is posted
regularly on comp.editors. You can also find a copy at
.PP
.Vb 1
\& http://www.faqs.org/faqs/editor\-faq/vi/part1/index.html
.Ve
.PP
Also, since Vim has gathered so many features in the last few years,
successfully documenting the frequently asked questions here is a
near-impossible task. To make it possible, please email the maintainer if
you have a good question. A good question is one that you've tried to
answer yourself (remember, Vim has great documentation) but struggled.
.SS "2.9. I have a patch for implementing a Vim feature. Where can I send this patch?"
.IX Subsection "2.9. I have a patch for implementing a Vim feature. Where can I send this patch?"
You can send your patches to the Vim developer mailing list
