.IX Subsection "11.4. How can I search/replace characters that display as '~R', '~S', etc.?"
You can use the 'ga' command to display the \s-1ASCII\s0 value/code for the
special character. For example, let us say the \s-1ASCII\s0 value is 142. Then you
can use the following command to search for the special character:
.PP
.Vb 1
\& /^V142
.Ve
.PP
where, ^V is entered by pressing CTRL-V.
.PP
For more information, read
