.SS "11.6. How do I search for whole words in a file?"
.IX Subsection "11.6. How do I search for whole words in a file?"
You can search for whole words in a file using the \e< and \e> atoms. For
example:
.PP
.Vb 1
\& /\e<myword\e>
.Ve
.PP
The \e< atom matches the beginning of the word and the \e> atom matches the
end of the word.
